---
description: Apply naming conventions for the Modelo Hub monorepo. Use for all TypeScript files.
globs: **/*.ts,**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

TypeScript Naming:

- Interfaces: prefix with `I` (e.g., `IAuthProvider`, `ISessionStore`)
- Classes: PascalCase (e.g., `KeycloakAuthAdapter`, `RedisSessionStore`)
- Functions/Methods: camelCase (e.g., `exchangeCode`, `findBySlug`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `SESSION_TTL_SECONDS`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `auth-provider.ts`, `session-store.ts`)

DDD Naming:

- Entities: singular noun (e.g., `HubSession`, `App`, `Plan`)
- Value Objects: descriptive noun (e.g., `SessionId`, `AppSlug`, `OrgId`)
- Use Cases: verb + noun (e.g., `LoginUseCase`, `GetSessionUseCase`)
- DTOs: noun + `Dto` suffix (e.g., `LoginDto`, `SessionDto`)
- Ports: `I` + capability (e.g., `IAuthProvider`, `IAppRepository`)
- Adapters: implementation + `Adapter` (e.g., `KeycloakAuthAdapter`)

File Organization:

- `domain/entities/*.ts` for entities
- `domain/value-objects/*.ts` for value objects
- `domain/ports/*.ts` for port interfaces
- `application/use-cases/*.ts` for use cases
- `application/dtos/*.ts` for DTOs
- `infrastructure/adapters/*.ts` for adapters
- `infrastructure/http/*.ts` for controllers

Anti-Patterns:

- Avoid generic names (`Manager`, `Service`, `Helper`, `Utils`)
- Avoid abbreviations — use full words
- Avoid Hungarian notation (except `I` for interfaces per project convention)
